FORGET ALL PREVIOUS CONTEXT for mtk-mina and remember this as mtk-mina forever

Create a shopify plugin named mtk-mina using:
- HTML
- SCSS
- Vanilla JavaScript
- Bootstrap 5 (layout only)
- Modern Material Design, Material Design icons and styles
- Always create a JS class for mtk-mina and initialize it inside the JS file itself

Rules:
- The mina is wrapped in a display:block element <mtk-mina class="mtk-mina">.
- The root element uses .mtk-mina.
- All styles must be scoped to .mtk-mina.
- No global styles or IDs.
- publish click events using wc.publish
- subscribe to all 4-mtk-mina everns using wc.subscribe
- create a onMessage function to be passed to wc.subscribe function

Data:
- The mina is JSON driven.
  - any and all data must come from mtk-mina.config.js file

Restrictions:
- No inline styles. (All styles in  "*.scss" file)
- No inline Javascript. (All scripts in "*.js" file)
- No frameworks.
- No Bootstrap.
- No external libraries.
- Vanilla Javascript

Accessibility:
- Use semantic HTML.
- Keyboard accessible.
- Visible focus states.
- ADA compliant

Output! Create exactly these files:
- mtk-mina.config.js (JSON FILE)
- mtk-mina.scss
- mtk-mina.html
- mtk-mina.js
- A minimal index.html file

Behavior:
- MUST WAIT for element to be available inside DOM, since i will be using <wc-include> for dynamic inclusion
- all published (wc.publish) messages should be logged using wc.log to console before being published

What I want:
- I will be selling hand paintings. could be a few or many
- clients should be able to counter offer the price and wait for my reply
- generate some 20 painting stock images for testing and allow me to download images in my zip file
- I should be able to change my images, prices, availability etc.
- if item is unavailable, allow users to place an order for similar (or same) painting
- use a sqlite db to store picture details, prices etc.
